3. Mathematical Formulations (ISST Core)
The Inverse-Square Scrape Theory (ISST) provides the mathematical backbone, quantifying information events (scrapes) based on energy, distance, entropy, and coherence.
A. Inverse-Square Decay (Base Signal)
The fundamental law states that the signal intensity (S) of an event decays inversely with the square of the distance (r) from the source, starting with an initial energy \left(E_0\right).
B. Full Intensity (Adjusted for Coherence and Entropy)
The full intensity formula adjusts the base decay using two critical modulation factors: Coherence (C) and Entropy (H).
 * Coherence \left(C\right) is a multiplier (it boosts the signal). High C means the signal is harmonically aligned (strong, clear).
 * Entropy \left(H\right) is a divisor (it attenuates the signal). High H means the signal is disordered/noisy. \alpha is a scaling constant.
C. Entropy and Coherence Calculations
These metrics quantify the quality and organization of the information scrape:
| Metric | Formula | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 3. Entropy (H) | H = - \sum p_i \log_2 p_i | Standard Shannon Entropy. Measures the randomness/disorder of the probability distribution (p_i) within the scrape. |
| 4. Coherence (C) | C = \frac{1}{N} \sum (\vec{v}_i \cdot \hat{n}) \cdot t_i | Measures vector/temporal alignment. It's the average of the projection of event vectors \left(\vec{v}_i\right) onto a normal \left(\hat{n}\right), weighted by time \left(t_i\right). |
D. Glyphs and Meta-Glyphs (Symbolic Cognition)
If a scrape's intensity S exceeds a certain threshold \left(\rho\right), it is compressed into an irreversible, cryptographic signature (Glyph G). Meta-Glyphs are created recursively from Glyphs when their collective coherence C_{\text{meta}} exceeds a higher threshold \left(\theta\right).
4. Repository Structure and Implementation
The repository is modular and focused on the theoretical and mathematical core of FPT and ISST.
| Directory/File | Focus Area | Key Functionality |
|---|---|---|
| /docs/theory/ | Foundation | Contains the core mathematical definitions of ISST (decay, entropy, coherence). |
| /src/scrape_theory/ | ISST Core Code | Implements the core logic: scrape_detector.py (entropy variance for perturbations), glyph_generator.py, and coherence.py. |
| /src/adversarial_defense/ | Application | isst_defense.py uses the ISST principles to create PyTorch-based defense layers for adversarial resilience. |
| /tools/ | Utilities | handshake_cli.py handles the RMP's receipt logging and verification. |
